<item>
            <title>[BCEL-239] Interfaces should not be used to define constants</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BCEL-239</link>
                <project id="12314220" key="BCEL">Commons BCEL</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Interfaces should not be used to define constants.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is often done as a way to save typing the name of a class that defines the constants. However using an interface pollutes any implementing classes with all the constant names, even if they are not used.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue applies to&lt;br/&gt;
Constants&lt;br/&gt;
ExceptionConstants&lt;br/&gt;
InstructionConstants&lt;/p&gt;</description>
